\subsection{Project Description and Summary (NEED GOAL, APPROACH, and
CONCLUSION AND THIS NEEDS TO BE ONE
PAGE?!!?)}\label{project-description-and-summary-need-goal-approach-and-conclusion-and-this-needs-to-be-one-page}}

The goal of this project is to find the most accurate model using a
variety of statistical model building techniques in order to predict
medical outcomes relating to breast cancer. We will use the BRCA
Multi-Omics (TCGA) data from Kaggle, and predict outcomes for the
\texttt{PR.Status}, \texttt{ER.Status}, \texttt{HER2.Final.Status}, and
\texttt{histological.type}. For our approach, we will first perform the
necessary data cleaning operations, then {[}method 1{]} and
{[}method2{]} to build classification models for \texttt{PR.Status} and
{[}method1{]} and {[}method2{]} for \texttt{histological.type}, using
classification error and AUC respectively as the evalution criteria.
Next, we will use {[}method{]} to build a model with the goal of
accurately predicting \textbf{all four} outcomes. Finally, {[}INSERT
CONCLUSION HERE{]}.

\hypertarget{pr.status}{%

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\FunctionTok{library}\NormalTok{(dplyr)}
\NormalTok{brca\_data }\OtherTok{=} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mgarbvs/STAT{-}432{-}final{-}project/main/cleaned\_brca\_data.csv"}\NormalTok{)}
\CommentTok{\# remove X.1 and X columns}
\NormalTok{brca\_data }\OtherTok{=}\NormalTok{ brca\_data }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%} \FunctionTok{select}\NormalTok{(}\SpecialCharTok{{-}}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"X.1"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"X"}\NormalTok{))}

\CommentTok{\# store the outcomes}
\NormalTok{outcomes }\OtherTok{=}\NormalTok{ brca\_data }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%} \FunctionTok{select}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"PR.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"ER.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"HER2.Final.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"histological.type"}\NormalTok{))}
\CommentTok{\# remove the categorical var temporarily}
\NormalTok{brca\_data }\OtherTok{=}\NormalTok{ brca\_data }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%} \FunctionTok{select}\NormalTok{(}\SpecialCharTok{{-}}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"PR.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"ER.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"HER2.Final.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"histological.type"}\NormalTok{))}

\CommentTok{\# Create a correlation matrix and select only variables with some correlation to the target}
\NormalTok{PR.Status }\OtherTok{=} \FunctionTok{as.numeric}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{as.factor}\NormalTok{(outcomes}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{PR.Status))}\SpecialCharTok{{-}}\DecValTok{1}
\NormalTok{pr\_data }\OtherTok{=} \FunctionTok{cbind}\NormalTok{(PR.Status, brca\_data)}

\NormalTok{pr\_data[}\FunctionTok{sapply}\NormalTok{(pr\_data, is.character)] }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{lapply}\NormalTok{(pr\_data[}\FunctionTok{sapply}\NormalTok{(pr\_data, is.character)], as.numeric)}


\CommentTok{\# head(pr\_data)}

\NormalTok{M }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{cor}\NormalTok{(pr\_data)}
\NormalTok{correlation\_threshold }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FloatTok{0.446}
\NormalTok{significant\_correlation }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{abs}\NormalTok{(M[}\StringTok{"PR.Status"}\NormalTok{, ]) }\SpecialCharTok{\textgreater{}}\NormalTok{ correlation\_threshold}
\FunctionTok{table}\NormalTok{(significant\_correlation)}

\FunctionTok{library}\NormalTok{(caret)}
\CommentTok{\# Linear regression model with selected features, 10 K{-}fold cross validation using the "caret" package {-}{-}{-}{-}{-}{-}{-}{-}{-}{-}{-}{-}{-}{-}}
\FunctionTok{set.seed}\NormalTok{(}\DecValTok{432}\NormalTok{)}

\DocumentationTok{\#\# 75\% of the sample size}
\NormalTok{smp\_size }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{floor}\NormalTok{(}\FloatTok{0.75} \SpecialCharTok{*} \FunctionTok{nrow}\NormalTok{(pr\_data))}

\DocumentationTok{\#\# set the seed to make your partition reproducible}
\NormalTok{train\_ind }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{sample}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{seq\_len}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{nrow}\NormalTok{(pr\_data)), }\AttributeTok{size =}\NormalTok{ smp\_size)}

\NormalTok{train\_y }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ outcomes}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{PR.Status[train\_ind]}
\NormalTok{pr\_train }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{cbind}\NormalTok{(train\_y, pr\_data[train\_ind, ])}
\NormalTok{pr\_train }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ pr\_train[, corr\_colnames]}

\CommentTok{\# Training parameters}
\NormalTok{ctrl }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{trainControl}\NormalTok{(}\AttributeTok{method =} \StringTok{"cv"}\NormalTok{,}
                     \AttributeTok{number =} \DecValTok{5}\NormalTok{,}
                     \AttributeTok{savePredictions =} \ConstantTok{TRUE}\NormalTok{,}
                     \AttributeTok{classProbs =} \ConstantTok{FALSE}\NormalTok{)}

\CommentTok{\# Fitting model}
\NormalTok{mod\_fit }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{train}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{as.factor}\NormalTok{(PR.Status) }\SpecialCharTok{\textasciitilde{}}\NormalTok{ ., }\AttributeTok{data=}\NormalTok{pr\_train,}
                 \AttributeTok{method=}\StringTok{"glm"}\NormalTok{,}
                 \AttributeTok{family=}\StringTok{"binomial"}\NormalTok{,}
                 \AttributeTok{trControl =}\NormalTok{ ctrl,}
                 \AttributeTok{tuneLength =} \DecValTok{5}\NormalTok{)}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\FunctionTok{library}\NormalTok{(dplyr)}

\CommentTok{\# remove X.1 and X columns}
\NormalTok{brca\_data }\OtherTok{=}\NormalTok{ brca\_data }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%} \FunctionTok{select}\NormalTok{(}\SpecialCharTok{{-}}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"X.1"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"X"}\NormalTok{))}

\CommentTok{\# store the outcomes}
\NormalTok{outcomes }\OtherTok{=}\NormalTok{ brca\_data }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%} \FunctionTok{select}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"PR.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"ER.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"HER2.Final.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"histological.type"}\NormalTok{))}
\CommentTok{\# remove the categorical var temporarily}
\NormalTok{brca\_data }\OtherTok{=}\NormalTok{ brca\_data }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%} \FunctionTok{select}\NormalTok{(}\SpecialCharTok{{-}}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"PR.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"ER.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"HER2.Final.Status"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"histological.type"}\NormalTok{))}

\CommentTok{\# Create a correlation matrix and select only variables with some correlation to the target}
